title: Measurement of the total neutron cross-section and resonance parameters of molybdenum using pulsed neutrons generated by an electron linac

resonance parameters of molybdenum using pulsed

x4freetext: Pohang Neutron Facility (PNF).
The PNF consists of an electron linac, a water-cooled
Ta target, and a 12 m long TOF path.
The neutron target was composed of ten Ta
plates with different thickness and a diameter of
4.9 cm, and the total length of neutron target is
The housing of the target was made of titanium.
This target was set at the center of a cylindrical
water moderator contained in an aluminum cylinder
with a diameter of 30 cm and a height of 30 cm.
A high purity (99.95%) natural Mo metallic plate
(10.20 g/cm3) with a diameter of 62.98 +- 0.01 mm
and a thickness of 2.96 +- 0.01 mm (0.01895 +-
0.00001 atoms/barn) was used as a transmission
sample.
The uniformity of the thickness is less than 0.3%.
The main impurities of this sample were W (<0.03%),
A set of notch filters of Co, In and Cd plates was
also used for the background measurement and the
energy calibration.
A 6Li-ZnS(Ag) scintillator (BC702) with a
diameter of 12.5 cm and a thickness of 1.6 cm has
been used as a neutron detector.
Only considered the statistical errors for the
measurements because the other sources of uncertaintie
which include the detection efficiencies,the geometric
factor for the sample, and the other systematic errors
are negligible.
Data are received from Dr.Guinyun Kim
